{"tid":2389320,"cid":5,"subCid":10,"title":"Starship Sn9遲遲不能試飛的原因 — SN8爆炸及「某些事件」違反了發射許可","createTime":"2021-01-31T21:44:49.000Z","updateTime":"2021-02-01T08:18:07.000Z","uid":295230,"like":3,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":11,"replies":[{"pid":"7c6a75014c9a91e48f78293db012b61aa1fad803","tid":2389320,"uid":295230,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-01-31T21:44:49.000Z","msg":"好放行啦喎屌你FAA<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/knife.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/knife.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/knife.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/knife.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/knife.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/knife.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/knife.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\n<strong>Elon Musk&rsquo;s SpaceX violated its launch license in explosive Starship test, triggering an FAA probe</strong><br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/HpaiCux.png\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2FHpaiCux.png&h=c8551143&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\nthe Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) &mdash; responsible for ensuring the safety of such spaceship launches &mdash; opened up an investigation into SpaceX's test flight. The agency found that the company had violated parts of its launch license, according to The Verge. Two sources &quot;familiar with the incident&quot; specified that <strong><span class=\"red\">the investigation looked into both the explosive landing and whether or not SpaceX complied with the FAA's guidelines.</span></strong><br />\n<br />\nThe newly uncovered violation helps to explain some of the recent tensions bubbling up between Musk and the FAA. <br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://twitter.com/elonmusk/status/1354862567680847876\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Felonmusk%2Fstatus%2F1354862567680847876&d=NiOc6rc%2FE9fikV